    <h1>Privacy Policy for Ghana Pulse</h1>
    <p class="post-meta">Effective Date: 2025-06-01</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to Ghana Pulse ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data with transparency. This Privacy Policy outlines what information we collect from visitors and users of our website (the "Site"), how we use it, with whom we share it, and your choices regarding the data. Please read this policy carefully.</p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <h3>a. Automatically Collected Information</h3>
    <p>When you visit our Site, we automatically collect certain information about your device, such as your web browser, IP address, time zone, and cookies installed on your device. We also collect information on pages you visit, how you arrived at the Site, and how you interact with it. This data is referred to as "Device Information."</p>
    <p>We collect this information through the following technologies:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Data files placed on your device that often include an anonymous unique identifier. More at <a href="http://www.allaboutcookies.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.allaboutcookies.org</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Log Files:</strong> These track actions on the Site and gather data such as your IP address, browser type, ISP, referring/exit pages, and timestamps.</li>
        <li><strong>Web Beacons, Tags, and Pixels:</strong> Used to track how you interact with the Site.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>b. Voluntarily Provided Information</h3>
    <p>We may also collect personal information you provide to us directly, such as your name, email address, or any details submitted through contact forms or newsletter subscriptions.</p>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Operate and maintain the Site</li>
        <li>Improve and personalize your experience</li>
        <li>Understand how users interact with our content</li>
        <li>Communicate with you, including updates and support</li>
        <li>Prevent fraudulent activity</li>
        <li>Deliver advertising, including personalized ads via Google AdSense</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Google AdSense and Advertising</h2>
    <p>We use Google AdSense to serve ads. AdSense uses cookies to deliver ads based on your visits to this and other sites on the internet.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Google uses cookies to serve ads on our Site.</strong></li>
        <li><strong>These cookies allow Google and its partners to serve ads based on your browsing history.</strong></li>
        <li>Other ad networks may also use cookies. Refer to their privacy policies for details.</li>
        <li>You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a> or <a href="http://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.aboutads.info/choices</a>.</li>
        <li>For more information, see <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">How Google uses information from sites or apps</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell or rent your personal data. We may share information with:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> For hosting, analytics, advertising, and customer service</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> If required by law or to comply with legal requests</li>
        <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We use reasonable security measures to protect your information. However, no online method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.</p>

    <h2>7. Your Data Protection Rights</h2>
    <p>You may have the following rights, depending on your location:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access, update, or delete your data</li>
        <li>Correct inaccuracies</li>
        <li>Object to processing</li>
        <li>Request restriction of processing</li>
        <li>Request data portability</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us using the information below.</p>

    <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our Site is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we learn that we have done so without verified parental consent, we will delete the data.</p>

